<title>CTO : Essay</title><link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="Recent Changes" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/recent-changes.rdf"><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722cs_/http://cliki.tunes.org/admin/cliki.css"></head><body><div id="banner"><a title="CTO" class="logo" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/">CTO</a> <span>CLiki for the TUNES project</span></div><div id="navbar"><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/index">Home</a> <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Recent%20Changes">Recent Changes</a> <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/CLiki">About CLiki</a> <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Text%20Formatting">Text Formatting</a> <a class="internal" onclick="if(name=window.prompt('New page name ([A-Za-z0-9 ])')) document.location='https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/edit/'+name ;return false;" href="/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/">Create New Page</a></div><div id="main"><h1>Essay</h1>Here are some rants, essays, and political perspectives on TUNES. This is its own <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/topic">topic</a>, so that anyone can automatically be indexed here. If you want to find your way through these papers, you should go to the TUNES <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Learning%20Lounge">Learning Lounge</a>.

<p><ul><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/As%20We%20May%20Think">As We May Think</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a>, Vannevar Bush's 1945 vision about what computers should become</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Blind%20Men%20and%20the%20Elephant">Blind Men and the Elephant</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> about the <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/TUNES%20Project">TUNES Project</a>, initiated by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/water">water</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/CDDB">CDDB</a> - <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a>'s <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> giving a nice, long, illustrative <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/example">example</a> of <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://tunes.org/new/Review/cddb.html">how Tunes should work</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Compiling%20and%20Translation">Compiling and Translation</a> - <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Essay">Essay</a>s by F</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/David%20Madore%20on%20TUNES">David Madore on TUNES</a> - David Madore wrote an <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://www.eleves.ens.fr:8080/home/madore/computers/tunes.html">overview of the project</a> from a nice laymen's perspective, in relatively-common terms</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Ethics%20and%20Information">Ethics and Information</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a>, by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/David%20Andel">David Andel</a>, commenting(?) Fare's article on <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://fare.tunes.org/articles/cybernethics.html">Ethics and Information</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Forth%20is%20NOT%20intrinsically%20slow">Forth is NOT intrinsically slow</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Kohlberg">Kohlberg</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Marc%20Santoro">Marc Santoro</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Learning%20Lounge%20Rebuilding">Learning Lounge Rebuilding</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Marc%20Santoro">Marc Santoro</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Linear%20Logic%20Comments">Linear Logic Comments</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Jack%20Waugh">Jack Waugh</a>:</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Mailing%20List%20Posts%20of%20Interest">Mailing List Posts of Interest</a> - This is a collection of <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a>s collecting notes from the past <em>several</em> years of <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://lists.tunes.org/archives/tunes/">the TUNES mailing list archives</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Migration%20Comparison">Migration Comparison</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a> explaining the Tunes concept of <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Migration">Migration</a>:</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/MPFAS">MPFAS</a> - "<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://fare.tunes.org/articles/ll99/index.en.html">Meta-Programming and the Free Availability of Sources</a>", an <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/No%20Proprietary%20Binary%20Data%20Formats">No Proprietary Binary Data Formats</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> which explain why proprietary data formats (especially binary, such as Word, WordPerfect, Excel etc) are bad</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Parenthetically-Speaking">Parenthetically-Speaking</a> - A great series of articles (topic: <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a>s) by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Kent%20M.%20Pitman">Kent M. Pitman</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Preemption%20and%20Cooperation">Preemption and Cooperation</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a> covering an area of the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://tunes.org/new/LLL/">LLL concepts</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/self-proclaimed%20%93hackers%94">self-proclaimed “hackers”</a> - A humorous <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/The%20Sieve%20of%20Erathostene">The Sieve of Erathostene</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a>, <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/example">example</a> of HLL concepts</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/The%20True%20Story%20of%20Ada">The True Story of Ada</a> - Essentially a political <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a></li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Trotskyite%20Tunes">Trotskyite Tunes</a> - A Revolutionary <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Essay">Essay</a>!</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/TUNES%20Dream%20Hardware">TUNES Dream Hardware</a> - A short descriptive <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a> about the hardware configuration that would suit a Tunes system the best:</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/TUNES%20vs%20the%20WWW">TUNES vs the WWW</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> which contrast the concepts of <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Metatext">Metatext</a> in Tunes with that of World Wide Web (WWW)</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Why%20a%20New%20OS">Why a New OS</a> - <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Fare">Fare</a>'s long, unfinished rationalizing <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> for TUNES</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Why%20GC">Why GC</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> concerning why <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/garbage%20collection">garbage collection</a> is essential to the Tunes project:</li><li><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/Word%20Processors%3A%20Stupid%20and%20Inefficient">Word Processors: Stupid and Inefficient</a> - An <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050319094722/http://cliki.tunes.org/essay">essay</a> by Allin Cottrell on the shortcomings of wordprocessors <em>vs</li></ul>
